{[%evp 0,38,16,19,26,32,24,-4,47,54,50,45,48,48,51,43,39,3,-3,-3,-3,5,16,27,23,0,0,0,0,-50,0,-41,0,0,0,-36,0,0,0,0,0]} 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bd7 5. Nf3 Bc6 6. Bd3 Nd7 7. O-O Ngf6 8. Neg5 {Concrete move. It's objectively not great for White, but Black needs to know the right reactions.} Bd6 $1 {the right development against 8.Neg5.} (8... Be7 $4 {would be a huge blunder because of} 9. Nxf7 $1 Kxf7 10. Ng5+ Kg8 11. Nxe6 Qc8 12. Re1 $18 {White's position is winning.}) 9. Re1 (9. Nxf7 $2 {doesn't work now because of} Kxf7 10. Ng5+ Ke7 11. Re1 Nf8 $19 {[%cal Gh7h6] h6 next, and our position is winning.}) (9. c4 {[%cal Yc4c5,Yd4d5] White wants c5 or d5.} h6 10. d5 $1 $146 {engine's strong idea, which allows White to stay in the game.} (10. Nh3 {sad move. Our position is already preferable after} Bxf3 (10... g5 $5 {also possible, but more risky.}) 11. Qxf3 c5 $1 $15 {[%csl Rh3]}) (10. Nxe6 $2 fxe6 11. Bg6+ Kf8 12. Re1 Kg8 $1 $19 {[%cal Gd7f8] Nf8 next, and White's position is lost.}) 10... exd5 11. Re1+ Kf8 12. cxd5 Bxd5 13. Ne4 Nxe4 14. Bxe4 Bxe4 15. Rxe4 Nc5 16. Re1 Qf6 $11 {White has compensation, but no more.}) (9. Qe2 h6 10. Ne4 {White's best option. It is almost the 8.Qe2 variation, but there are some differences because our bishop is on d6 and not on e7.} (10. Nxe6 $2 fxe6 11. Bg6+ Kf8 12. Qxe6 Bd5 $1 $17 {key move.}) (10. Nh3 Bxf3 11. Qxf3 O-O $1 $146 12. Qxb7 c5 $36 {Black already has the initiative. For example:} 13. c3 (13. Qc6 Qb8 $1 $15 {[%csl Rh2][%cal Gd6h2]}) 13... cxd4 14. cxd4 Nd5 $36) 10... Nxe4 (10... O-O $5 {also fine.} 11. Nxd6 cxd6 $132 {[%cal Gf8e8,Ge6e5] Re8-e5 will be our plan.}) 11. Bxe4 Bxe4 12. Qxe4 c6 $11 {no problem for Black.}) 9... h6 $1 {only move, otherwise our position is lost.} 10. Nh3 (10. Nxe6 $2 fxe6 11. Bg6+ Ke7 {[%cal Gd7f8] Nf8 next.} 12. Rxe6+ Kxe6 13. Qe2+ Ne4 14. c4 Qe7 $1 15. d5+ Kf6 16. Bxe4 Rae8 $19) (10. Rxe6+ $5 {this amazing move, is actually possible.} Kf8 $1 {critical move.} (10... fxe6 11. Nxe6 Qc8 12. Nxg7+ Kf7 13. Nf5 Be4 $1 {only move.} 14. Bc4+ Nd5 15. Nxh6+ Kg7 16. Ne5 $1 N7b6 17. Qh5 Qe6 18. Qg5+ Bg6 19. Bd3 Bxe5 20. dxe5 Raf8 {we are not worse, but White has full compensation. For example} 21. g4 $5 $44) 11. Rxd6 {only move.} cxd6 12. Nh3 g5 $1 $15 {White has some compensation, but objectively our position is slightly better.} 13. Nd2 {Howell-Rustemov.} (13. Ne1 Be4 $1 $15) 13... Qb6 $1 $146 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gb6d4] important idea.} 14. c3 Bb5 $1 $15) (10. Ne4 {safe move, but for sure not an ambitious one.} Bxe4 11. Bxe4 Nxe4 12. Rxe4 Nf6 13. Re1 c5 $11 {Just equal.}) 10... Bxf3 $1 {necessary move. White will have two bishops, but the knight on h3 is misplaced, and we can create a fast counterplay with c7-c5.} (10... O-O $4 {huge mistake because of} 11. Ne5 $1 $16 {You should always be careful about allowing the Ne5 idea.}) 11. Qxf3 O-O $5 {My recommendation. The idea is to play c7-c5 in one move.} (11... c6 {has been an almost automatic move so far. It's also possible, but also White can play. For example:} 12. Nf4 Qa5 $1 (12... O-O 13. Nh5 $1 $36 {some small initiative for White.}) 13. c3 O-O {more or less playable. For the engine, this is equal. The key point is that Black will be in time to play e6-e5.} (13... O-O-O $6 14. b4 Qc7 15. g3 $14 {Risky for Black.}) 14. Bd2 (14. Bc2 e5 $1 $11) (14. Qh3 Rfe8 $11 {[%cal Ge6e5] e5 next.}) 14... e5 $1 $11) 12. g4 $5 $146 {looks critical.} (12. Nf4 c5 $1 13. dxc5 {we can recapture with the knight or with the bishop, but also} Qa5 $5 {[%csl Re1][%cal Ga5e1] is possible.} 14. c3 Qxc5 $11) (12. Qxb7 $6 c5 $44 {Full compensation, we have already seen this idea.}) (12. c3 c5 $1 $132) 12... c5 $1 13. g5 hxg5 14. Nxg5 (14. Bxg5 $6 {objectively dubious, but interesting.} cxd4 15. Qg2 Re8 16. Kh1 {[%cal Ge1g1] White's idea is to play on the 'g' file, but we have a nice idea:} Kf8 $1 $15 {[%csl Ye7][%cal Gf8e7] Our king will go to e7, and it's very safe there.}) 14... Qa5 15. Re2 cxd4 16. Qh3 Rfe8 $1 {White is not worse just because he can force a draw by repetition:} 17. Bd2 Qc7 18. Bh7+ Kf8 19. Bd3 Kg8 $11 {logical outcome of a game where both sides have followed engine's recommendations.} *

