{[%evp 0,36,28,20,42,33,33,2,42,45,41,49,49,49,49,49,56,23,22,4,5,6,0,-15,0,-8,3,16,11,15,6,15,22,14,-2,-2,-8,-20,-7]} 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bd7 5. Nf3 Bc6 6. Bd3 Nd7 7. O-O Ngf6 8. Nxf6+ {hamrless move, but it has been played more than 600 times.} Qxf6 $1 {the correct recapture.} (8... Nxf6 $6 {most common, but slightly dubious.} 9. Re1 {[%cal Gc2c3,Gf3e5] White's idea is c3-Ne5.} (9. Ne5 Qxd4 $1 $11 10. Nxf7 $4 Qd5 $1 $19 {key idea.}) 9... Be7 10. c3 {[%cal Gf3e5] White will be much better if he manages to play Ne5.} Bxf3 {necessary.} 11. Qxf3 Qd5 12. Qh3 $1 $14 {very unpleasant for Black.}) 9. Be2 {necessary move to defend f3.} (9. c3 $2 {bad strategic decision.} Bxf3 $1 10. Qxf3 Qxf3 11. gxf3 Nf6 $15 {[%csl Rf2,Rf3] Black is already better thanks to White's spoiled structure.}) 9... Bd6 (9... h6 {is also very often played, but there is no need to be scared about Bg5.}) 10. c4 {[%cal Gd4d5] Critical move. White's idea is d5.} (10. c3 O-O $11 {[%cal Gf8e8,Ge6e5] Rfe8-e5 next, and our position is very fine.}) (10. Bg5 {both Qf5 or Qg6 are good.} Qf5 $5 (10... Qg6 $11 {also good.}) 11. Bh4 O-O 12. Bg3 Rfd8 $11 {no problem for Black.} (12... a5 $5 {[%cal Ga5a4] We can also take space on the queenside.})) 10... Be4 {[%cal Ge4g6] Known idea. We will rotate our bishop on g6, in real Caro-Kann spirit.} (10... Bxf3 $6 11. Bxf3 c6 12. g3 $14 {[%cal Gf3g2,Gc1e3] It's also playable, but White has a risk-free game.}) (10... b6 $5 {[%cal Gc6b7] rare but good. The position is just equal.}) 11. Bg5 (11. Ng5 Bg6 12. Be3 (12. f4 $6 {was tried in 5 games, but it's dubious:} Rd8 $36 {[%cal Ge8g8,Gc7c5] We will play for 00-c5.}) 12... O-O 13. c5 (13. f4 $6 c5 $1 $15) (13. Bd3 h6 14. Nf3 Bh5 $1 $132 {No problem for Black in Nakamura-Duda, 2022.}) 13... Bf4 14. Nf3 $1 {We have many options, but White is not worse.} (14. Nh3 $6 Bxe3 15. fxe3 Qe7 16. Bf3 e5 $36 {Sax-Epishin, 1992.}) 14... e5 {The simplest.} (14... Be4 $5) (14... Rad8 $5) 15. Qb3 Be4 $11) 11... Qf5 {White has different options.} 12. Be3 {The hope is that Be4 will be misplaced, and Ng5 is already an idea.} (12. Bh4 Bf4 $5 $132 {[%cal Gg7g5] g5 next, with a very interesting game.}) (12. Qd2 h6 13. Be3 (13. Bh4 O-O 14. Bg3 b6 $11) 13... O-O $11 {no problem for Black.}) 12... h6 $1 {[%cal Rf3g5] We prevent Ng5.} 13. Rc1 {White prevents Bc2.} (13. Nd2 Bc2 14. Qc1 c6 $11) 13... O-O 14. Nd2 Bc6 $1 (14... Bd3 15. Bxd3 Qxd3 {Looks very normal for Black, but White has a tactical idea:} 16. Qf3 $36 c6 $4 {most logical move, but it's losing due to} 17. Ne4 $1 {key move.} Be7 18. Rfd1 $18 {[%csl Rd3]}) 15. Bg4 Qg6 16. Bf3 Bxf3 17. Qxf3 c6 18. Ne4 Bc7 $11 {Black was completely fine in Adams-Plakeza, 2019.} *

