{[#]} {[%tqu "En","Critical moment, Black to move.","","","a7a5","I like this move. We want to take space on the queenside.",10,"c6f3","is not good now because the d4 pawn is defended.",0,"b7b6","is Black's most common move, but I am not a big fan of it:",0]} 10... a5 $5 {[%cal Ga5a4] I like this move. We want to take space on the queenside.} (10... Bxf3 $6 {is not good now because the d4 pawn is defended.} 11. Qxf3 c5 12. Qxb7 $14 {[%csl Yd4][%cal Yc3d4]}) (10... b6 {is Black's most common move, but I am not a big fan of it:} 11. Bf4 $5 Bb7 12. Qe2 c5 13. Rad1 Qc8 14. dxc5 Nxc5 15. Bc2 $14 {White's pieces are well placed. We can still play after, for example, Qc6-Rfe8-Rad8, but White is sligthly better.}) 11. Qe2 a4 $132 {[%csl Ga4] It's a novelty, but it's also a very logical continuation of our previous move. The position is fresh and interesting.} *

